modules.description: Provides functions for creating, querying, and updating key-value stores using hash tables. Operates on strings as keys and values, with support for persistent storage through file-based serialization. Used to manage configuration settings and session data in applications requiring fast lookups and durability.

Provides operations to open and close a database, retrieve, insert, update, and delete key-value pairs, and iterate over keys. Works with a custom database handle type `t` and string-based key-value storage. Used for managing persistent data in applications requiring fast key-based lookups and modifications.
